During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney addressed several topics including the recent violence in Afghanistan, the President's decision-making on post-2014 forces in Afghanistan, the progress on the President's second-term agenda, gun control legislation, North Korea, the importance of the families of Newtown victims in the gun control debate, the timing of immigration reform, the passing of former British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher, and the President's support for marriage equality. Carney also discussed the possibility of filibustering nominees, recent oil spills, and the Israeli-Palestinian conflict.